FuncDef:
The end-group command concludes the configuration of a QPPB configuration group, exits the QPPB configuration group view, and returns to the system view.
By default, the end-group command is not run.
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
By default, routes do not carry the QoS attribute. Configuring QPPB helps collect traffic statistics. To conclude the configuration of a QPPB configuration group, exit the QPPB configuration group view, and return to the system view, run the end-group command.
Prerequisites
Apply clauses have been configured for a QPPB configuration group.
